
collection of numbers,
find the matching pair that == sum

[1,2,3,9] SUM 8
[1,2,4,4] SUM 8

clarify the result
[1,2,3,9] SUM 8 No
[1,2,4,4] SUM 8 Yes

clarify the input
- array of values
- sorted
- repetable values
- negative and positive

solution 1 compare everything with everything.
for loop with inner for loop, want tru elements of array, sum them and print the suo of pairs == SUM

disadvantages time compexity is n^2

solution 2  we could use a binary search tofin for each element a pair that  ==  SUM - element using binary search, that will be n log N

solution 3 we could compare a pairs of elements, starting form first and last index of an array,
if sum of pair is > than SUM,
	move right index to left
if sum if pairs < SUM
  move left index to right
if sum of == sum
	print
	move left index to right

time complexity O(n)


findPairsWithSum(data:int[], sum:int) : -> bool
	left_index = 0
	right_index = len(data) - 1
	while (left_index < right_index){
		pair_sum = data[left_index] + data[right_index]
		if pair_sum == sum:
		  return true
		if pair_sum > sum:
			left_index++
		else
			right_index--

	returun false

No longer sorted


bool findPairsWithSum(data:int[], sum:int) :